02/11/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan met with visiting Bulgarian Deputy Prime Minister Emel Etem on Wednesday (November 1st) about a relaxed visa regime for Turkish citizens after Bulgaria joins the EU on January 1st.
Citing strong investor interest in Bulgaria, Ankara wants relaxed visa requirements for Turkish businessmen.
Erdogan also voiced his country's willingness to learn from Bulgaria's experience in the EU accession process.
(BNR, BTA - 01/11/06)
